function twoCitySchedCost(costs) {
    costs.sort((a, b) => (a[0] - a[1]) - (b[0] - b[1]));

    let totalCost = 0;
    const n = costs.length / 2;

    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        totalCost += costs[i][0] + costs[i + n][1];
    }

    return totalCost;
}
```

    1. Sort the costs by the difference between the cost of flying to city A and city B. This will effectively prioritize the people who may benefit most from flying to a particular city.
2. Calculate the total cost by adding the costs for the first half of the sorted list flying to city A, and the latter half flying to city B.
3. Return the total cost as the result.

This greedy algorithm minimizes the total cost by selecting the closest suitable matchings for each city, ensuring that we get the lowest possible cost across all possibilities.

